---
layout: post
title:  'A better approach to manipulation CSS with JavaScript'
date:   2015-08-03 09:00:00
tags: ['javascript', 'ui', 'design', 'css']
---

Usually when you want to manipulate the CSS of some elements on a page, you wait for the document to load and then apply the new CSS to all elements that match some rule. A better approach, when CSS styles depend on the window size, woule be to be able to change the CSS rules once the document head was loaded.

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6620393/is-it-possible-to-alter-a-css-stylesheet-using-javascript-not-the-style-of-an
http://www.quirksmode.org/dom/changess.html
